A gambler has the opportunity to make bets on the outcomes of a sequence of coin flips. If the coin comes up heads, the gambler wins as many dollars as they have staked; if it is tails, they lose their stake. The game ends when the gambler reaches their goal of $100 or loses all their money. The objective is to find the optimal policy that maximizes the probability of reaching the goal. ï¿¼ ï¿¼

